==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Australian ballot
<hw>Aus*tra"li*an bal"lot</hw>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A system of
balloting or voting in public elections, originally used in South
Australia, in which there is such an arrangement for polling votes that
secrecy is compulsorily maintained, and the ballot used is an official
ballot printed and distributed by the government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

